# Test Engineer at Nortal

At Nortal, we are committed to creating solutions with a significant impact. Our projects drive digital transformation across various industries, including government, healthcare, telecom, and enterprise. With over 20 years of experience, we have a proven track record of building a Seamless Society, positively affecting more than half a billion lives globally.

We operate in 26 locations across Europe, North America, and the GCC region, offering a hybrid work environment that balances flexibility with strong local connections.

## Role Overview

We are seeking a highly skilled Quality Automation Engineer with 2+ years of experience to join our dynamic team. You will play a crucial role in ensuring the quality and reliability of our software products by designing, implementing, and executing automated testing solutions. Effective communication and collaboration with clients are essential, and travel or in-person work may be required based on client engagements and internal events. This is a hybrid role requiring office attendance 3 days per week.

## Responsibilities

### General Coding & Development
- Expert in multiple programming languages with knowledge of major frameworks and libraries.
- Understands basic design patterns and is proficient in setting up CI/CD pipelines and applying DevSecOps and Quality Engineering best practices.
- Knowledgeable in various programming methodologies (functional vs. object-oriented, imperative vs. declarative) and their applications.
- Experienced in testing RESTful APIs using tools like Postman and SoapUI.

### Teaming & Consulting
- Demonstrates clear and concise written and verbal communication.
- Acts professionally with clients and maintains a positive, collaborative attitude.
- Articulates and follows Agile principles; participates actively in scrums, planning, and retrospective meetings.
- Completes project work timely, adds value at project and team levels, and advocates for best practices.

### Solution Design
- Identifies and applies technical solutions to project work.
- Provides feedback, proposes improvements, and implements new tools and frameworks for application testing.
- Analyzes and understands flows and end-to-end interactions in distributed systems.

## Qualifications

### Must Have
- **Cloud:** AWS
- **Languages:** Java, Spring, SQL
- **Quality & Testing:**
  - Experience in writing automation, performance, integration, and end-to-end tests.
  - Testing across backend, frontend, web, and mobile applications.
  - Proficiency in defining and communicating the benefits of various quality automation toolsets.
  - Experience with JUnit and/or NUnit for unit testing.
  - Skilled in automated testing using Selenium, Playwright, Jest, Jasmine, or similar tools.
  - Troubleshooting issues with deployed systems and improving code quality and design guidelines.
  - Hands-on experience with RESTful APIs and testing them using Postman and SoapUI.
- **Agile Methodologies:** Experience with Agile environments, Scrum or Kanban, prioritizing tasks, and managing sprints.
- **CI/CD and DevOps:** Familiarity with DevOps practices and tools (Git, CI/CD pipelines) and integration with testing efforts.

### Some Working Knowledge Required
- **CI/CD and DevOps:** Docker, Kubernetes; specifically, their integration in testing.

### Nice to Have
- **Certifications:**
  - ISTQB Test Automation Engineering Certification
  - IST Certified Software Test Automation Specialist (CSTAS) Certification

